Inter Milan President Steven Zhang has hit out at Serie A president Paolo Dal Pino over the league’s rescheduling of fixtures as a result of the novel coronavirus outbreak. Italy is currently battling the largest outbreak of the virus in Europe, with more than 2,000 people confirmed to be infected. READ ALSO:  coronavirus: 6 more cases linked to UAE Tour A number of top-flight games in Italy have been affected by the outbreak, including Inter’s top-of-the-table clash against Juventus which was called off last weekend. Juventus fans wear protective masks during their side’s Champions League clash against Lyon.